{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b5087f40-04ad-43b5-b509-81fe2d4b4004","content":"No pipeline files found in the repo, so here's a general migration guide.\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) doesn't use `vstest.console`; it runs via `dotnet test`. Replace:\n\n```yaml\n# ❌ Old – VSTest@3\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```yaml\n# ✅ New – dotnet test with MTP\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **TRX reports** – Use `--logger \"trx\"` to produce `.trx` files, then publish them:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n   ```\n\n2. **Code coverage** – Use `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (requires `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` or `coverlet`), then publish:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     condition: always()\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n\n3. **Project setup** – Ensure each test `.csproj` has:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n### Why this works\n\n- MTP builds the test host into the project itself (`Exe` output), so `vstest.console` is no longer needed.\n- `dotnet test` detects MTP-enabled projects automatically and delegates to the built-in runner.\n- TRX logging and coverage collection are handled via the same CLI flags as before.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a417175-ce44-4b5f-88d4-66d211ecfdb4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No pipeline files found. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":632,"requestId":"480F:23D333:3123FFC:35BAE45:69FBE2F5"},"id":"a3e1e078-c366-4f6d-8f49-a14b2e694573","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:55:30.261Z","parentId":"7885127b-6b72-45c2-b8c7-aca6ff20cc3f"}
